#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.48"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.48:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.48:0.2"
msgid "5. Akkosavagga"
msgstr "5. Abuse"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 48. Pabbajitaabhiṇhasutta → dasadhammasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an10.48:0.3"
msgid "48. Pabbajitaabhiṇhasutta"
msgstr "48. Ten Regular Reflections for a Renunciate"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:1.1"
msgid "“Dasayime, bhikkhave, dhammā pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, one who has gone forth should often reflect on these ten things."

msgctxt "an10.48:1.2"
msgid "Katame dasa?"
msgstr "What ten?"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:2.1"
msgid ""
"‘Vevaṇṇiyamhi ajjhupagato’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (1)"
msgstr ""
"One who has gone forth should often reflect: ‘I have achieved freedom from "
"class.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.88"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:3.1"
msgid ""
"‘Parapaṭibaddhā me jīvikā’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (2)"
msgstr "‘My livelihood is tied up with others.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:4.1"
msgid "‘Añño me ākappo karaṇīyo’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (3)"
msgstr "‘My behavior should be different.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:5.1"
msgid ""
"‘Kacci nu kho me attā sīlato na upavadatī’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (4)"
msgstr ""
"‘I hope there’s no reason to blame myself when it comes to ethical conduct?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:6.1"
msgid ""
"‘Kacci nu kho maṃ anuvicca viññū sabrahmacārī sīlato na upavadantī’ti "
"pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (5)"
msgstr ""
"‘I hope that, after examination, sensible spiritual companions don’t "
"reproach any aspect of my ethics?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:7.1"
msgid ""
"‘Sabbehi me piyehi manāpehi nānābhāvo vinābhāvo’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (6)"
msgstr "‘I must be parted and separated from all I hold dear and beloved.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:8.1"
msgid "‘Kammassakomhi kammadāyādo kammayoni kammabandhu kammapaṭisaraṇo, "
msgstr ""
"‘I am the owner of my deeds and heir to my deeds. Deeds are my womb, my "
"relative, and my refuge."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:9.1"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kammaṃ karissāmi kalyāṇaṃ vā pāpakaṃ vā tassa dāyādo bhavissāmī’ti "
"pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (7)"
msgstr "I shall be the heir of whatever deeds I do, whether good or bad.’"

# BB: “How am I spending my nights and days”, Thanissaro: “What am I becoming as the days & nights fly past?”, Rhys Davids: “As days and nights pass quickly by, how have they found me? and how left?”, Piyadassi: “How do I spend my nights and days?” Kathambhuta only occurs twice elsewhere in the suttas, and in both cases it clearly means “what sort “of”. I think this is a reflection about a perspective on how you” re changing as life goes on, not just “did I do my meditation this morning!”
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:10.1"
msgid ""
"‘Kathaṃbhūtassa me rattindivā vītivattantī’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (8)"
msgstr "‘As the days and nights flit by, what sort of person am I becoming?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:11.1"
msgid ""
"‘Kacci nu kho ahaṃ suññāgāre abhiramāmī’ti pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ "
"paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (9)"
msgstr "‘Do I love to stay in empty huts?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
#. VAR: yenāhaṃ → sohaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1) | yohaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an10.48:12.1"
msgid ""
"‘Atthi nu kho me uttari manussadhammo alamariyañāṇadassanaviseso adhigato, "
"yenāhaṃ pacchime kāle sabrahmacārīhi puṭṭho na maṅku bhavissāmī’ti "
"pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbaṃ. (10)"
msgstr ""
"‘Do I have any superhuman distinctions in knowledge and vision worthy of the "
"noble ones, so that when my spiritual companions question me on my deathbed "
"I will not be embarrassed?’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an10.48:13.1"
msgid ""
"Ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa dhammā pabbajitena abhiṇhaṃ paccavekkhitabbā”ti."
msgstr "One who has gone forth should often reflect on these ten things.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.48:13.2"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
